properties.areaDesc: Kaibab Plateau; Coconino Plateau; Little Colorado River Valley in Coconino County; Grand Canyon Country; Western Mogollon Rim
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 2 at 3:00AM MST until February 3 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts to 60 mph. Gusts
65 to 70 mph possible near the San Francisco peaks and the
Doney Park area.

* WHERE...Much of Coconino County including the Kaibab Plateau,
Grand Canyon Village, Cameron, Flagstaff, Doney Park.

* WHEN...From Sunday evening through early monday morning.

* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property
and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult especially
for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A period of snow showers is likely to
develop as the winds begin to decrease early Monday morning and
into the afternoon.
properties.instruction:
People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown
around or damaged by the wind.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 AM MST MONDAY
